This paper deals with analyzing the effects of gender signals and performance in online product reviews, which falls under the category of computational social science (cs.CY). The paper also involves natural language processing techniques and deep learning classifiers, which are commonly used in sub-categories such as cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The study also involves analyzing user behavior and preferences, which can be associated with sub-categories such as cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing).
